<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc41a35e8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7805"><num value="7805">§ 7805.</num><heading> Revolving fund</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The revolving fund shall be deposited in a checking account with the Treasury of the United States. Such amounts thereof as the Secretary may determine to be necessary to establish and maintain operating accounts for the various canteens may be deposited in checking accounts or other interest-bearing accounts in other depositaries selected by the Secretary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc41a35e9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1250">72 Stat. 1250</ref>, § 4205; <ref href="/us/pl/100/322/tIV/s414/a/1">Pub. L. 100–322, title IV, § 414(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1988-05-20">May 20, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/549">102 Stat. 549</ref>; renumbered § 7805 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/a">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(a)</ref>, (b)(1), <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s4/b/1">Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(b)(1)</ref>, (2)(E), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404">105 Stat. 404</ref>, 405.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc41a35ea-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
